Geoffrey Onyeama, Minister of Foreign Affairs in Nigeria, has tested positive for Coronavirus. The minister, who made this known on Sunday via his verified Twitter handle, said his fourth Covid-19 test returned positive on Saturday. He said he had felt slight itching in his throat and had had his samples collected for Covid-19 test. Nigeria Foreign Affairs Minister, Geoffrey Onyeama.
Reuters “Did my fourth Covid-19 test yesterday at the first sign of a throat irritation and unfortunately this time it came back positive. That is life! Win some lose some. Heading for isolation in a health facility and praying for the best. #StayHomeSaveLives #COVID19 #PTFCOVID19,” he tweeted.  Did my fourth Covid-19 test yesterday at the first sign of a throat irritation and unfortunately this time it came back positive. That is life! Win some lose some. Heading for isolation in a health facility and praying for the best. #StayHomeSaveLives #COVID19 #PTFCOVID19  Onyeama is the first minister to contract the disease under the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari.